tes or until a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of the cake comes out mostly clean (the texture of this loaf is sticky, so the skewer will still have some crumbs). Allow to cool in tin for 10 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely. Serve plain or with butter, or transfer into a sealable container until ready to use (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can soak your fruit for up to 24 hours. The longer the fruit soaks the plumper it will be, resulting in a very moist loaf.","You can use any quantity of the dried fruits listed to make a total weight of 300 g.","You can store this malt loaf in a sealable container for up to 5 days."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 20m","12 portions"]}